name: Novak Djokovic
summary: Novak Djokovic, despite recently undergoing knee surgery, is making a strong start at Wimbledon. He has already triumphed in his first match, drawing praise from Roger Federer who believes he can shatter all records. Despite his injury, Djokovic is pushing the boundaries of Wimbledon's all-white policy with his black sleeve. He secured a victory in the second round despite the home crowd's support for his opponent. Djokovic's resilience is evident in his determination to compete, despite his injury and the early exit of other competitors. With his sights set on the title, Djokovic hopes to cement his dominance at Wimbledon, making him one to watch in the upcoming matches.

name: Kesha
summary: Kesha has released her first independent single titled "Joyride," marking a new chapter in her music career after parting ways with her former labels. The song, which incorporates elements of country, was inspired by Tennessee and Dolly Parton. Kesha celebrates her newfound independence and a special Independence Day in the track. The lyrics express a sense of liberation and empowerment. "Joyride" is the first single Kesha has released since settling her legal battle with Dr. Luke, and it has received positive reactions from fans and critics alike.

name: Hatch recall
summary: Hatch Baby has issued a recall for nearly 919,000 power adapters used in their Rest 1st Generation sound machines following concerns over shock hazards. The recall, announced by the Consumer Product Safety Commission, impacts adapters sold with the sound machines from September 2016 through October 2022. The issue stems from a small number of cases where the adapters overheated, posing a potential electrical shock hazard. Consumers are advised to immediately stop using the recalled power adapters and contact Hatch Baby for a free replacement.
